title: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<?>) classSet is not expected class
description: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<?>) The output is 'MySomeClass'.
OB: The output is 'MySomeClass', but I expect the output to be 'MySomeClass'. This issue is not yet implemented in the Servlet 3.0 specification. I have tested my code on Glassfish 3.0 and it works fine there.
EB: The classSet is not the expected class as per the Servlet 3.0 specification.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:  
  1. Use ServletContainerInitializer in a codebase.  
  2. Implement the onStartup method with the set of classes.  
  3. Verify the output to see if it matches the expected behavior.
